<h1>Requirements and restrictions for borrowed activations </h1>
<p>Borrowing an activation requires a network connection, but once the activation is borrowed to a particular computer, the computer can be disconnected from the network. </p>
<p>When a borrowed activation expires, the software on the computer will no longer be activated and the activation automatically becomes available again from the server's activation pool (no network connection is required).</p>
<p>A borrowed activation can be manually returned to the activation server before the borrow term expires, but this requires a network connection.</p>
<p>A borrowed FlexNet Publisher (FNP) activation can only activate local applications installed on the same machine, not applications installed on another virtual or physical machine. </p>
<table class="tableintopic">
<tr>
<td>
<p class="tableheading"><strong>Tips:</strong></p>
</td>
<td><ul>
<li>Borrowed activations are not supported by all products. See product documentation for details.</li>
<li>Borrowed activations are not supported on client computers using Remote Desktop Services or Terminal Services client access licenses.</li>
</ul></td>
</tr>

</table>
